<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetConsole.OpenConsoleHandle" Title="OpenConsoleHandle method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.LogTargetConsole">LogTargetConsole</PageRef> ->
    OpenConsoleHandle
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>OpenConsoleHandle</TypeRef> method opens a handle to the attached Windows console output device.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        This method opens <TypeRef>CONOUT$</TypeRef>. It does not allocate a new console for the process.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[bool OpenConsoleHandle();]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Return value">
      <ReturnValue Type="bool">
        <TypeRef>true</TypeRef> if a console handle is already open or was opened successfully; otherwise <TypeRef>false</TypeRef>.
      </ReturnValue>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
